{"lemma":"ذَبِيحٌ","slug":"ذَبِيحٌ","root":"ذ.ب.ح","root_slug":"ذ-ب-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ب-ح","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13688"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AD%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13688","headword_ar":"ذَبِيحٌ","root":"*bH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*obuwHN","text_ar":"مَذْبُوحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divided, lengthwise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see 1]. (S, Msb, K, TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misokN *abiyHN","text_ar":"مِسْكٌ ذَبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHN faA^oratuhu","text_ar":"ذَبِيحٌ فَاْرَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Musk of which the follicle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vesicle, is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ripped open."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A. [It is there said to be tropical: but see 1.]) ―         -b2-  Both are [also] applied to an animal, (Msb,) or a sheep or goat, (TA,) [or an animal of the ox-kind, and a sheep or goat, and the like, (see 1,)] as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Slaughtered, in the manner described in the first paragraph of this art.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHN","text_ar":"ذَبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHapN","text_ar":"ذَبِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below:]) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHN","text_ar":"ذَبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a fem. epithet without the addition of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN *abiyHN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ ذَبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabo$N *abiyHN","text_ar":"كَبْشٌ ذَبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHN","text_ar":"ذَبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an instance of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; though you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Ap *abiyHapN","text_ar":"شاة ذَبِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also; and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the pl. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHN","text_ar":"ذَبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aboHaY","text_ar":"ذَبْحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abaAHaY","text_ar":"ذَبَاحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHapN","text_ar":"ذَبِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abaAy^iHu","text_ar":"ذَبَايِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Aboo-Dhu-eyb says, describing wine,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yuqaAlu lahaA damu Alwadaji Al*~abiyHu"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma*obuwHu Eanohu","text_ar":"المَذْبُوحُ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One would call it the blood of the external jugular vein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for which it had been slit"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to let it flow]. (AAF, TA.) And again he says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wasirobK taTal~aY biAlEabiyri kaA^an~ahu\n                      \n                     \n                        dimaA='u ZibaA='u biAln~uHuwri *abiyHu"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And many a bevy of women rubbed over with perfume compounded with saffron, as though it were the blood of gazelles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the gazelles whereof had been"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaughtered in the upper parts of the breasts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: he applies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*byH","text_ar":"ذبيح"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dmA='","text_ar":"دما=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHN ZibaAw^uhu","text_ar":"ذَبِيحٌ ظِبَاوُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he applies it as an epithet to a pl. n. because it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], for such an epithet is applicable to masc. and fem. and sing. and pl. nouns. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abiyHN","text_ar":"ذَبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An animal that is fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, to be slaughtered as a sacrifice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is destined, or prepared, for sacrifice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an intended victim;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iboHN","text_ar":"ذِبْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as appears from the fact that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~abiyHu","text_ar":"الذَّبِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is (assumed tropical:)  a surname of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ismá'eel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ishmael;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) for, accord. to some [or rather the generality] of the Muslims, he was the son whom Abraham designed to sacrifice, though others say it was Isaac: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA A@bonu","text_ar":"اَنَا ا@بْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~abiyHayoni","text_ar":"الذَّبِيحَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a trad. [as said by Mohammad, meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am the son of the two intended victims;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ismá'eel and 'Abd-Allah"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; for 'Abd-El-Muttalib incurred the obligation to sacrifice his son 'Abd-Allah, the father of the Prophet, by reason of a vow, and ransomed him with a hundred camels. (K, * TA.) ―         -b4-  Also (tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slain man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","ISk","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}